HEADWORD: Spokeshave
<hw>Spoke"shave`</hw> <pr>(sp⟦omac⟧k"sh⟦amac⟧v`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A kind of drawing knife or planing tool for dressing the spokes of
wheels, the shells of blocks, and other curved work.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

